The paper focuses on recommending venues on location-based social networks, which falls under the category of information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also discusses collaborative filtering and learning to rank, which are common topics in machine learning (cs.LG). The use of similarity measures based on venues' contents and locations suggests a focus on spatial information (cs.SI) and database management (cs.DB). Finally, the paper discusses the social aspect of location-based social networks, which could fall under the category of social and information networks (cs.SOC).
